title: COMP1511 Course Review
summary: COMP1511 is UNSW's introduction to programming course, which teaches C and is arguably the best COMP course, here is my review.

title: MATH1131 Course Review
summary: MATH1131 is usually the first math course taken, covering a linear algebra and calculus component. It is an extension to highschool mathematics, but goes more in depth, here is my review.

title: COMP1521 Course Review
summary: COMP1521 is UNSW's Computer Systems Fundamentals, which covers lower level abstraction compared to COMP1511's C. It uses C and teaches MIPS which is an assembly language.

title: MATH1231 Course Review
summary: MATH1231 is a continuation from the course MATH1131. It covers linear algebra and calculus content and in addition, it touches on an introduction to statistics and uses Maple as a mathematical computing software, here is my review.

title: COMP2521 Course Review
summary: COMP2521 covers data structures and algorithms and is essential to a computer scientist, this course had its ups and downs, here is my review.

title: COMP1531 Course Review
summary: COMP1531 is a dreaded course for most students since it requires group work, however it is a great introduction to software engineering and teaches useful content, like JavaScript and Git, here is my review.

title: MATH1081 Course Review
summary: MATH1081 or Discrete Mathematics is a course fundamental to computer scientists as it tackles topics like number theory, combinatorics and graph theory, here is my review.
